The 34th smallest country in the world, by land area, is Saint Kitts and Nevis. It is a small island nation located in the Caribbean Sea, with a total land area of approximately 261 square kilometers. The country is known for its beautiful beaches, lush rainforests, and historic sites, including Brimstone Hill Fortress National Park, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Its economy is based primarily on tourism, agriculture, and light manufacturing.